WEBVTT

00:00:01.042 --> 00:00:03.667
[♪♪♪]

00:00:03.667 --> 00:00:06.626
<i>♪ Ninjago ♪</i>

00:00:07.417 --> 00:00:10.375
[♪♪♪]

00:00:16.375 --> 00:00:17.876
[METAL CLANGING]

00:00:17.876 --> 00:00:20.042
[KAI GRUNTS]

00:00:20.876 --> 00:00:23.209
To forge
the perfect weapon,

00:00:23.209 --> 00:00:25.042
you first need
the right metal

00:00:25.042 --> 00:00:26.417
and plenty of heat.

00:00:26.417 --> 00:00:27.501
Cool it off...

00:00:27.501 --> 00:00:30.209
[WATER HISSING]
and...

00:00:30.209 --> 00:00:32.459
presto. Aw.

00:00:32.459 --> 00:00:33.167
[LAUGHS]

00:00:33.167 --> 00:00:34.209
You made it too quickly,
Kai.

00:00:34.209 --> 00:00:37.209
Be patient. If Father
was still here, he’d say--

00:00:37.209 --> 00:00:39.751
I know. "No matter how much
fire you have,

00:00:39.751 --> 00:00:42.792
experience isn’t something
you learn overnight."

00:00:42.792 --> 00:00:43.667
That may work for you, Nya,

00:00:43.667 --> 00:00:47.876
but I’m gonna be a better
blacksmith than Dad ever was.

00:00:47.876 --> 00:00:48.334
Hm.

00:00:48.334 --> 00:00:53.000
Your metal is loud and heavy,
useful to slow one down.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.042
Useless
in the art of stealth.

00:00:56.042 --> 00:00:58.834
All tools for a samurai,

00:00:58.834 --> 00:01:01.918
but nothing for a ninja?

00:01:01.918 --> 00:01:02.417
Ninja? Ha!

00:01:02.417 --> 00:01:05.667
You’re a long way from finding
a ninja in these parts, old man.

00:01:05.667 --> 00:01:09.334
And the shop is called Four
Weapons, not "Four" Browsing.

00:01:09.334 --> 00:01:10.042
Either buy something

00:01:10.042 --> 00:01:13.042
or go peddle your insults
somewhere else.

00:01:13.042 --> 00:01:13.709
Ha! Too bad.

00:01:13.709 --> 00:01:17.584
Thought I’d find something
special here.

00:01:17.584 --> 00:01:22.334
If it’s something special
you’re looking for,

00:01:22.334 --> 00:01:23.959
let me sh--

00:01:23.959 --> 00:01:27.292
NYA:
What is it?

00:01:27.292 --> 00:01:29.417
He was just...

00:01:29.417 --> 00:01:32.584
Forget it.

00:01:37.292 --> 00:01:40.375
[ENGINES WHIRRING]

00:01:41.417 --> 00:01:43.375
Oh, oh,
let me go first!

00:01:43.375 --> 00:01:44.417
Please, oh please!

00:01:44.417 --> 00:01:46.167
I’m dying
to go down there.

00:01:46.167 --> 00:01:48.709
You nitwit,
you’re already dead.

00:01:48.709 --> 00:01:53.083
Try to control yourself
in front of Master Samukai.

00:01:53.083 --> 00:01:56.000
Uh, with all due respect,

00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:59.042
last time you did say
that I could go first.

00:01:59.042 --> 00:02:02.083
Sorry, boys,
this one is mine.

00:02:02.083 --> 00:02:07.459
Just remember what we’re after,
and find that map.

00:02:07.459 --> 00:02:09.501
Attack!

00:02:09.501 --> 00:02:12.209
[TIRES SCREECH]

00:02:12.209 --> 00:02:14.167
ALL:
Attack!

00:02:14.167 --> 00:02:15.626
Boo!

00:02:15.626 --> 00:02:18.250
[ALL SCREAM]

00:02:22.209 --> 00:02:23.167
What are they?

00:02:23.167 --> 00:02:26.292
I don’t know. Stay here.

00:02:28.417 --> 00:02:29.834
[GROWLS]

00:02:29.834 --> 00:02:32.167
[GRUNTING]

00:02:34.876 --> 00:02:37.459
[BITING]
Ow!

00:02:37.459 --> 00:02:38.709
Bite this!

00:02:38.709 --> 00:02:41.125
Ah!

00:02:44.334 --> 00:02:46.667
I thought I told you
to stay back.

00:02:46.667 --> 00:02:48.667
And what?

00:02:49.584 --> 00:02:52.042
Let you have all the fun?

00:02:52.042 --> 00:02:54.417
[GRUNTING]

00:02:55.999 --> 00:02:56.667
Hm.

00:02:56.667 --> 00:02:59.918
You’re not looking
hard enough.

00:02:59.918 --> 00:03:01.250
[GRUNTS]

00:03:01.250 --> 00:03:01.834
Ow!

00:03:01.834 --> 00:03:04.792
You’re not looking
hard enough!

00:03:04.792 --> 00:03:08.000
[BOTH GRUNTING]

00:03:13.542 --> 00:03:14.459
[GASPS]

00:03:14.459 --> 00:03:16.417
BOTH:
The map!

00:03:18.626 --> 00:03:21.042
Ha-ha!

00:03:21.042 --> 00:03:23.375
[CHUCKLES]

00:03:23.375 --> 00:03:24.959
Oops.

00:03:28.459 --> 00:03:30.292
[YELLS]

00:03:34.209 --> 00:03:37.334
WU:
Ninjago!

00:03:41.459 --> 00:03:42.626
Sensei Wu?

00:03:42.626 --> 00:03:44.918
Your spinjitzu looks rusty.

00:03:44.918 --> 00:03:49.626
Nothing like bone
to sharpen it’s edge, Samukai.

00:03:49.626 --> 00:03:51.292
[KAI GRUNTS]

00:03:53.584 --> 00:03:55.626
[LAUGHS]

00:03:59.083 --> 00:04:01.542
[♪♪♪]

00:04:01.542 --> 00:04:04.209
Oh, no.
Ninjago!

00:04:07.709 --> 00:04:10.999
Lord Garmadon
says take the girl.

00:04:10.999 --> 00:04:13.125
Lord Garmadon?

00:04:13.125 --> 00:04:15.250
[LAUGHS]

00:04:16.501 --> 00:04:17.751
[SCREAMS]

00:04:17.751 --> 00:04:19.584
Nya!

00:04:19.584 --> 00:04:22.125
[SAMUKAI CACKLING]

00:04:24.334 --> 00:04:25.918
They took Nya.

00:04:25.918 --> 00:04:27.125
I told you.

00:04:27.125 --> 00:04:28.667
Useless.
Oh!

00:04:28.667 --> 00:04:30.000
You could have
done something!

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:33.667
You could have used your--
Your twistitzu, or your-- Your--

00:04:33.667 --> 00:04:35.125
Spinjitzu.

00:04:35.125 --> 00:04:36.209
But you did nothing.

00:04:36.209 --> 00:04:38.125
I’m gonna get
my sister back.

00:04:38.125 --> 00:04:40.918
Where they go,
a mortal cannot.

00:04:40.918 --> 00:04:43.751
That was Samukai,
king of the Underworld.

00:04:43.751 --> 00:04:47.626
And if it’s true
that he’s carrying out orders

00:04:47.626 --> 00:04:49.375
for Lord Garmadon,

00:04:49.375 --> 00:04:51.417
then I fear things
are far worse

00:04:51.417 --> 00:04:52.459
than I had ever thought.

00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:56.501
Lord Garmadon? Underworld?
What’s going on?

00:04:56.501 --> 00:04:58.918
What do we have
that’s so important to them,

00:04:58.918 --> 00:05:01.000
and why would they
take my sister?

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:03.501
What’s so important?

00:05:03.501 --> 00:05:07.792
How about everything
in Ninjago itself.

00:05:07.792 --> 00:05:10.083
<i>Long before time had a name,</i>

00:05:10.083 --> 00:05:14.000
<i>Ninjago was created
by the first spinjitzu master</i>

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:18.292
<i>by using the four weapons
of spinjitzu:</i>

00:05:18.292 --> 00:05:19.959
<i>the Scythe of Quakes,</i>

00:05:19.959 --> 00:05:22.000
<i>the Nunchuks of Lightning,</i>

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:23.792
<i>the Shurikans of Ice</i>

00:05:23.792 --> 00:05:26.459
<i>and the Sword of Fire.</i>

00:05:26.459 --> 00:05:28.042
<i>Weapons so powerful</i>

00:05:28.042 --> 00:05:31.834
<i>no one can handle
all of their power at once.</i>

00:05:31.834 --> 00:05:34.083
<i>When he passed away,</i>

00:05:34.083 --> 00:05:36.709
<i>his two sons swore
to protect them.</i>

00:05:36.709 --> 00:05:40.292
<i>But the oldest was consumed
by darkness</i>

00:05:40.292 --> 00:05:43.000
<i>and wanted to posses them.</i>

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:46.042
<i>A battle between brothers
broke out,</i>

00:05:46.042 --> 00:05:50.292
<i>and the oldest was struck down
and banished to the Underworld.</i>

00:05:50.292 --> 00:05:55.375
<i>Peace returned, and the younger
brother hid the weapons.</i>

00:05:55.375 --> 00:05:57.584
<i>But knowing
his older brother’s</i>

00:05:57.584 --> 00:05:59.459
<i>relentless ambition
for power,</i>

00:05:59.459 --> 00:06:02.250
<i>he placed a guardian
to protect them.</i>

00:06:02.250 --> 00:06:05.209
<i>And for fear
of his own demise,</i>

00:06:05.209 --> 00:06:08.459
<i>a map for an honest man
to hide.</i>

00:06:08.459 --> 00:06:11.876
That honest man
was your father.

00:06:11.876 --> 00:06:15.167
The older brother
is Lord Garmadon.

00:06:15.167 --> 00:06:20.334
And I need to find those weapons
before he does.

00:06:20.334 --> 00:06:22.167
Y-you’re the younger brother?

00:06:22.167 --> 00:06:24.459
Then you came here
looking for the map?

00:06:24.459 --> 00:06:28.876
No. I came for something
greater: you.

00:06:28.876 --> 00:06:32.167
Since my brother
cannot enter this realm,

00:06:32.167 --> 00:06:35.959
it’s obvious he has struck
a deal with Samukai.

00:06:35.959 --> 00:06:38.999
If he were to collect
all four weapons,

00:06:38.999 --> 00:06:42.667
even I would not be able
to stop him again.

00:06:42.667 --> 00:06:46.667
But you,
you have the fire inside.

00:06:46.667 --> 00:06:50.417
I will train you to harness it,
use it,

00:06:50.417 --> 00:06:52.709
become a spinjitzu master.

00:06:52.709 --> 00:06:56.876
Look, I’m flattered
you think I’m all that.

00:06:56.876 --> 00:06:57.999
But I gotta save my sister,

00:06:57.999 --> 00:07:01.375
not get involved
in your sibling rivalry.

00:07:01.999 --> 00:07:02.792
Ha-ha! Clunky mule.

00:07:02.792 --> 00:07:06.000
You are not even ready
to face my pinky toe.

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:07.250
[GRUNTING]
If you want

00:07:07.250 --> 00:07:10.792
to get your sister back,
you must control the fire

00:07:10.792 --> 00:07:12.125
that burns inside.

00:07:12.125 --> 00:07:13.375
[GRUNTING]
Only when you become

00:07:13.375 --> 00:07:18.417
a spinjitzu master
will you be able to face

00:07:18.417 --> 00:07:21.000
Lord Garmadon.

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.542
Okay.

00:07:22.542 --> 00:07:24.584
Then when do we start?

00:07:24.584 --> 00:07:27.959
[GRUNTING]

00:07:36.876 --> 00:07:38.667
How long is this training
gonna be?

00:07:38.667 --> 00:07:42.709
Aren’t we in a little bit of
a rush since they have the map?

00:07:42.709 --> 00:07:45.292
Patience.

00:07:47.876 --> 00:07:50.334
You will be ready
when you are ready.

00:07:50.334 --> 00:07:51.834
Not a minute sooner.

00:07:51.834 --> 00:07:54.250
[PANTING]

00:07:54.250 --> 00:07:55.292
A monastery?

00:07:55.292 --> 00:07:58.459
You expect me to learn to fight
in a place of peace?

00:07:58.459 --> 00:08:01.417
Not fight. Train.

00:08:01.417 --> 00:08:02.667
To become a true ninja,

00:08:02.667 --> 00:08:06.584
first you must be able
to see what others do not.

00:08:06.584 --> 00:08:09.417
But there’s nothing here.

00:08:24.959 --> 00:08:25.959
Whoa.

00:08:25.959 --> 00:08:29.083
Is this gonna teach me
how to do that cool move?

00:08:29.083 --> 00:08:31.584
[GRUNTS]

00:08:32.584 --> 00:08:34.709
Oh, dear.

00:08:34.709 --> 00:08:37.292
[SCREAMS]

00:08:37.292 --> 00:08:40.876
Complete the training course
before I finish my tea,

00:08:40.876 --> 00:08:44.834
then we will see
if you are ready.

00:08:46.501 --> 00:08:48.751
[SLURPS]

00:08:48.751 --> 00:08:50.626
Today you failed.

00:08:50.626 --> 00:08:52.375
Tomorrow you will
try again.

00:08:52.375 --> 00:08:55.709
Failed? But I didn’t
even start to--

00:08:56.918 --> 00:08:59.626
Patience.

00:09:00.584 --> 00:09:03.626
[♪♪♪]

00:09:16.250 --> 00:09:18.209
Failed.

00:09:21.918 --> 00:09:23.626
Failed.

00:09:23.626 --> 00:09:24.709
[GRUNTING]

00:09:24.709 --> 00:09:27.000
WU:
Oh, failed.

00:09:28.834 --> 00:09:30.250
Oh, so failed.

00:09:30.250 --> 00:09:32.459
[♪♪♪]

00:09:42.125 --> 00:09:44.834
Ha-ha!

00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:46.959
Ah!

00:09:46.959 --> 00:09:48.751
And...

00:09:48.751 --> 00:09:50.584
failed.

00:09:57.459 --> 00:09:59.999
[♪♪♪]

00:10:13.918 --> 00:10:17.459
Was that one sugar or two?

00:10:17.459 --> 00:10:18.501
Ha!

00:10:18.501 --> 00:10:20.209
So am I gonna learn
this spinjitzu

00:10:20.209 --> 00:10:21.417
I’ve been hearing
so much about?

00:10:21.417 --> 00:10:25.459
You already have.
Your final test comes tomorrow.

00:10:25.459 --> 00:10:26.792
Huh?
My advice

00:10:26.792 --> 00:10:28.876
is to get some sleep.

00:10:31.334 --> 00:10:34.250
[♪♪♪]

00:10:34.250 --> 00:10:36.292
[SNORING]

00:10:39.167 --> 00:10:39.999
[TOOTHBRUSH BUZZING]

00:10:39.999 --> 00:10:42.667
WU:
<i>My advice is to get some sleep.</i>

00:10:42.667 --> 00:10:45.000
Oh, yeah? Well, take this.

00:10:45.000 --> 00:10:47.876
[GRUNTING]

00:10:47.876 --> 00:10:49.751
And this!

00:10:51.501 --> 00:10:53.417
And this!

00:10:54.209 --> 00:10:55.375
Oops.

00:10:55.375 --> 00:10:57.918
[♪♪♪]

00:11:04.959 --> 00:11:07.042
[YELLS]

00:11:07.042 --> 00:11:08.584
[LAUGHS]

00:11:08.584 --> 00:11:11.584
[GRUNTS]

00:11:11.584 --> 00:11:13.083
Ah!

00:11:31.125 --> 00:11:34.292
WU:
Stop!

00:11:34.834 --> 00:11:36.584
NINJAS:
Yes, sensei.

00:11:36.584 --> 00:11:40.999
Wait a minute,
they’re your students too?

00:11:41.125 --> 00:11:42.959
This was my final test,
wasn’t it?

00:11:42.959 --> 00:11:44.250
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

00:11:44.250 --> 00:11:47.083
You never said anything
about a fourth.

00:11:47.083 --> 00:11:47.918
It’s always three.

00:11:47.918 --> 00:11:50.459
Three blind mice,
three musketeers, three--

00:11:50.459 --> 00:11:51.751
What he’s trying to say,
Sensei Wu,

00:11:51.751 --> 00:11:54.417
is that the three of us
have trained together.

00:11:54.417 --> 00:11:55.292
We’re solid.

00:11:55.292 --> 00:11:57.626
Didn’t look so solid
to me.

00:11:57.626 --> 00:11:59.334
Master, what is
the meaning of this?

00:11:59.334 --> 00:12:01.584
Each of you
have been chosen.

00:12:01.584 --> 00:12:05.250
Each in tune
with elemental properties.

00:12:05.250 --> 00:12:06.918
But first.

00:12:06.918 --> 00:12:09.042
Ninjago!

00:12:11.417 --> 00:12:14.626
KAI:
Whoa! How’d he do that?

00:12:14.626 --> 00:12:15.584
Look what color I am.

00:12:15.584 --> 00:12:18.042
Wait a minute.
I’m still black.

00:12:18.042 --> 00:12:20.751
Kai, master of fire.

00:12:20.751 --> 00:12:23.834
It burns bright in you.

00:12:23.834 --> 00:12:25.792
Jay is blue.
Master of lightning.

00:12:25.792 --> 00:12:28.751
Heh! That’s not all
I’m the master of.

00:12:28.751 --> 00:12:31.209
I do a little inventing,
I dabble in model-building,

00:12:31.209 --> 00:12:33.167
touch of cooking,
a little poetry--

00:12:33.167 --> 00:12:35.250
More like mouth of lightning.

00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:37.792
Black ninja is Cole.

00:12:37.792 --> 00:12:42.918
Solid as rock.
Master of earth.

00:12:42.918 --> 00:12:43.667
Ha!

00:12:43.667 --> 00:12:44.667
Nice to meet you, kid.

00:12:44.667 --> 00:12:46.667
I got your back.
And for the record,

00:12:46.667 --> 00:12:50.125
there ain’t nothing
in this world I’m afraid of.

00:12:50.125 --> 00:12:50.876
Except for dragons.

00:12:50.876 --> 00:12:55.584
Dragons aren’t from this world,
Zane. I said in this world.

00:12:55.584 --> 00:12:57.792
And white ninja is Zane.

00:12:57.792 --> 00:13:02.751
Master of ice
and seer with sixth sense.

00:13:02.751 --> 00:13:06.626
I sense this one takes things
a little too seriously.

00:13:06.626 --> 00:13:08.999
You too have the gift?
[LAUGHS]

00:13:08.999 --> 00:13:10.792
He’s just making
a joke, Zane.

00:13:10.792 --> 00:13:14.167
Remember what we talked about?
Your sense of humor? Huh?

00:13:14.167 --> 00:13:16.918
Yes. It was a joke.
Ha, ha.

00:13:16.918 --> 00:13:18.876
WU:
Pay attention!

00:13:19.501 --> 00:13:21.584
You four are the chosen ones

00:13:21.584 --> 00:13:23.375
who will protect
the four weapons

00:13:23.375 --> 00:13:26.584
of spinjitzu
from Lord Garmadon.

00:13:26.584 --> 00:13:28.250
But what about my sister?
[GASPS]

00:13:28.250 --> 00:13:31.125
We’re saving a girl?
Is she hot?

00:13:31.125 --> 00:13:31.959
Jay!

00:13:31.959 --> 00:13:32.959
I-- I just wanna know

00:13:32.959 --> 00:13:34.792
what we’re getting
ourselves into.

00:13:34.792 --> 00:13:36.626
Does she like blue?
Back off.

00:13:36.626 --> 00:13:40.375
When we find the weapons,
we will find your sister.

00:13:40.375 --> 00:13:41.375
It is time.

00:13:41.375 --> 00:13:43.709
We must go
to the first weapon.

00:13:43.709 --> 00:13:44.501
Whoa, hold on a minute.

00:13:44.501 --> 00:13:46.751
You said you were gonna
teach us spinjitzu.

00:13:46.751 --> 00:13:50.334
Spinjitzu is inside
each and every one of you.

00:13:50.334 --> 00:13:51.834
But it will only be unlocked

00:13:51.834 --> 00:13:55.709
when the key
is ready to be found.

00:13:55.709 --> 00:13:57.709
Come. My feet are tired.

00:13:57.709 --> 00:13:59.792
We will take
the horse carriage.

00:13:59.792 --> 00:14:00.501
Great.

00:14:00.501 --> 00:14:02.167
Now we have to find
a key?

00:14:02.167 --> 00:14:02.709
Yeah.

00:14:02.709 --> 00:14:04.459
I’m feeling like
he’s taking us for a ride.

00:14:04.459 --> 00:14:09.250
Well, if it means finding
my sister, then sign me up.

00:14:09.250 --> 00:14:11.626
[♪♪♪]

00:14:12.918 --> 00:14:14.584
[ALL PANTING]

00:14:14.584 --> 00:14:16.042
"Sign me up."

00:14:16.042 --> 00:14:17.209
Way to go, spark plug.

00:14:17.209 --> 00:14:21.501
I sense this is some strange
form of team-building.

00:14:21.501 --> 00:14:22.918
Just keep pulling.

00:14:22.918 --> 00:14:24.209
We have a long way to go.

00:14:24.209 --> 00:14:27.125
So where did sensei
find you three?

00:14:27.125 --> 00:14:29.501
Let’s just say if it wasn’t
for Sensei Wu,

00:14:29.501 --> 00:14:32.000
I don’t think we would
ever be seen together.

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:34.000
<i>I was testing my limits.</i>

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:36.667
[GRUNTING]

00:14:36.667 --> 00:14:38.459
Ha-ha! Huh?

00:14:38.459 --> 00:14:41.000
I was testing
my invention.

00:14:42.542 --> 00:14:43.876
Whoa! Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

00:14:43.876 --> 00:14:46.876
Whoa!
[CRASHING]

00:14:46.876 --> 00:14:48.584
[GROANING]

00:14:49.999 --> 00:14:55.125
ZANE:
<i>And I was testing myself.</i>

00:14:55.125 --> 00:14:57.000
Hm?

00:14:59.584 --> 00:15:00.334
You’re right.

00:15:00.334 --> 00:15:03.292
If it weren’t for sensei,
none of us would--

00:15:03.292 --> 00:15:05.834
Shh! Stop.

00:15:05.834 --> 00:15:07.375
The caves of despair.

00:15:07.375 --> 00:15:11.667
Samukai must be close to
unearthing the Scythe of Quakes.

00:15:11.667 --> 00:15:16.417
Remember, do not use the weapon,
for it’s power--

00:15:16.417 --> 00:15:18.876
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
is too much for us mortals.

00:15:18.876 --> 00:15:21.834
All right, guys, let’s
chop-socky this lemonade stand.

00:15:21.834 --> 00:15:23.250
Cole, you got the plan?
Sure do.

00:15:23.250 --> 00:15:25.709
First we lower ourselves
down the ledge,

00:15:25.709 --> 00:15:26.999
and then--

00:15:26.999 --> 00:15:28.709
Where’s Kai?

00:15:35.167 --> 00:15:37.709
JAY:
Let’s go.

00:15:44.417 --> 00:15:47.083
[SKELETONS MUMBLING
INDISTINCTLY]

00:15:56.667 --> 00:15:58.292
Ow! Oh!

00:15:58.292 --> 00:16:00.417
[GROANS]

00:16:05.876 --> 00:16:08.209
[PUNCHES LANDING]

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:14.876
KAI [GASPS]:
The map.

00:16:14.876 --> 00:16:16.375
[GASPING]

00:16:16.375 --> 00:16:17.834
I found something!

00:16:17.834 --> 00:16:20.417
That’s another rock,
you bonehead.

00:16:20.417 --> 00:16:22.626
But it’s shaped
like a doughnut.

00:16:22.626 --> 00:16:26.375
Mm, I wonder
if it tastes like--

00:16:26.375 --> 00:16:27.834
Oh!

00:16:27.834 --> 00:16:29.792
[SIGHS]

00:16:43.292 --> 00:16:46.167
[WHISPERING]
What’s the matter with you?

00:16:46.167 --> 00:16:48.125
Shh!

00:16:49.334 --> 00:16:50.584
[LAUGHS]

00:16:50.584 --> 00:16:52.292
JAY:
It’s upside down.

00:16:52.292 --> 00:16:54.042
They’re digging
in the wrong spot.

00:16:54.042 --> 00:16:57.751
The golden weapon
is near.

00:17:00.584 --> 00:17:03.542
There’s no time to waste.

00:17:03.542 --> 00:17:05.083
What is it
with that guy?

00:17:05.083 --> 00:17:06.959
Always in a rush.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:13.584
[GROANING]

00:17:14.042 --> 00:17:16.459
Hey. Before you
race off again,

00:17:16.459 --> 00:17:18.584
you need to remember
we’re a team.

00:17:18.584 --> 00:17:20.876
Yeah. Whatever.

00:17:20.876 --> 00:17:23.083
[ALL GROAN]

00:17:27.918 --> 00:17:31.501
JAY:
Whoa! That is so cool!

00:17:31.501 --> 00:17:35.751
[ECHOING]
<i>Cool, cool, cool.</i>

00:17:35.751 --> 00:17:37.584
Shh!

00:17:37.584 --> 00:17:39.167
Not so loud.

00:17:39.167 --> 00:17:40.792
Oh, come on,
don’t be paranoid.

00:17:40.792 --> 00:17:44.292
We’re totally on the opposite
side of the caves.

00:17:44.292 --> 00:17:45.125
Zip it, okay?

00:17:45.125 --> 00:17:46.292
Now that we’ve got
the Scythe,

00:17:46.292 --> 00:17:50.167
let’s sneak out while those
boneheads are still busy.

00:17:52.334 --> 00:17:54.709
All right, team,
everyone stick together.

00:17:54.709 --> 00:17:57.501
The way out
is right around the corner--

00:17:57.501 --> 00:17:59.000
Ah!

00:18:02.083 --> 00:18:05.751
[SKELETONS SHOUTING
AND GRUMBLING]

00:18:05.751 --> 00:18:07.834
[♪♪♪]

00:18:07.834 --> 00:18:08.751
[YELLS]

00:18:08.751 --> 00:18:10.042
Ha-ha, two points!

00:18:10.042 --> 00:18:12.709
Kai, throw it here.

00:18:13.334 --> 00:18:15.709
COLE:
Going long!

00:18:16.584 --> 00:18:19.876
There’s too many of them.
Let me handle it.

00:18:19.876 --> 00:18:21.959
[YELLING]

00:18:22.334 --> 00:18:27.209
Hey, guys, it’s just like
the training course.

00:18:27.209 --> 00:18:29.918
Over the planks,
dodge the swords,

00:18:29.918 --> 00:18:31.667
here comes the dummy.

00:18:31.667 --> 00:18:33.751
Cha-ching!

00:18:35.751 --> 00:18:37.626
KAI:
Spinjitzu.

00:18:37.626 --> 00:18:39.501
Jay, what’s the key?

00:18:39.501 --> 00:18:40.083
[LAUGHING]

00:18:40.083 --> 00:18:41.834
I’m just going
through the motions,

00:18:41.834 --> 00:18:43.334
This is what sensei
must have meant

00:18:43.334 --> 00:18:44.542
when he said
we already know it.

00:18:44.542 --> 00:18:49.375
Over the planks, dodge the
swords, here comes the dummy.

00:18:49.375 --> 00:18:50.125
[LAUGHING]

00:18:50.125 --> 00:18:52.334
He just called you
a dummy.

00:18:52.334 --> 00:18:54.876
No, he called you a dummy.

00:18:54.876 --> 00:18:57.292
[BOTH SCREAM]

00:18:57.459 --> 00:19:00.209
I sense you do not
stand a chance.

00:19:00.209 --> 00:19:01.959
Retreat!

00:19:01.959 --> 00:19:03.792
[ALL SCREAM]

00:19:05.334 --> 00:19:10.375
COLE:
Ha! Guess they didn’t want a
second serving of these babies.

00:19:10.375 --> 00:19:14.667
Good thing they didn’t check out
the merchandise in the back.

00:19:14.667 --> 00:19:16.501
KAI [LAUGHS]:
All right!

00:19:16.501 --> 00:19:17.417
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

00:19:17.417 --> 00:19:20.751
[GROWLING]
COLE: Uh, guys?

00:19:20.751 --> 00:19:22.042
ZANE:
Didn’t sensei say

00:19:22.042 --> 00:19:25.459
there was a guardian
protecting the weapons?

00:19:25.459 --> 00:19:27.042
COLE:
Is that a--?

00:19:27.042 --> 00:19:29.209
That’s not what I think it is,
is it?

00:19:29.209 --> 00:19:30.334
JAY:
You mean a dragon?

00:19:30.334 --> 00:19:32.167
KAI:
That sure looks like a dragon.

00:19:32.167 --> 00:19:36.375
I sense we won’t be able to spin
our way out of this one.

00:19:37.209 --> 00:19:39.584
[ROARS]
[ALL SCREAM]

00:19:42.959 --> 00:19:46.584
KAI:
I thought dragons
weren’t from this world.

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:50.584
No, no, Kai. Bad idea.
Sensei told us not to.

00:19:50.584 --> 00:19:53.542
Then you better
keep your mouth shut.

00:19:53.542 --> 00:19:56.334
COLE:
Kai! Don’t!

00:20:02.501 --> 00:20:04.709
[♪♪♪]

00:20:04.709 --> 00:20:07.000
COLE:
We gotta escape.

00:20:07.792 --> 00:20:09.751
We’ll use spinjitzu.

00:20:09.751 --> 00:20:11.584
[ROARS]

00:20:11.584 --> 00:20:14.209
[ALL GRUNT]
COLE: Ninjago!

00:20:16.667 --> 00:20:18.876
[COLE SCREAMS]

00:20:18.876 --> 00:20:19.501
[ALL GRUNT]

00:20:19.501 --> 00:20:23.083
COLE: That was so awesome!
KAI [LAUGHING]: Yes.

00:20:23.083 --> 00:20:24.501
We are unbelievable.

00:20:24.501 --> 00:20:26.626
ZANE:
We are the best

00:20:26.626 --> 00:20:27.459
Ha! Did you see that?

00:20:27.459 --> 00:20:30.125
I was like, pow,
and you were like, bam!

00:20:30.125 --> 00:20:31.876
WU:
Enough!

00:20:31.876 --> 00:20:35.083
I told you not to use
the Scythe.

00:20:35.083 --> 00:20:36.334
He did it.
What?

00:20:36.334 --> 00:20:37.542
I warned him, sensei.

00:20:37.542 --> 00:20:39.083
Using it
was my only option.

00:20:39.083 --> 00:20:41.709
And what makes you think
you are more important

00:20:41.709 --> 00:20:43.834
than the team, huh? Huh?

00:20:43.834 --> 00:20:46.000
They took my sister,
remember?

00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:48.709
There are still
three weapons left.

00:20:48.709 --> 00:20:51.709
Maybe next time
you can do it right.

00:20:54.083 --> 00:20:56.292
[♪♪♪]

00:21:03.584 --> 00:21:06.834
Master, I have failed you.

00:21:06.834 --> 00:21:09.375
They have learned spinjitzu.

00:21:09.375 --> 00:21:11.125
And they have the Scythe.

00:21:11.125 --> 00:21:12.626
GARMADON:
Good.

00:21:12.626 --> 00:21:14.459
Then my brother
was there.

00:21:14.459 --> 00:21:18.542
If I gather my army,
we can easily ambush them and--

00:21:18.542 --> 00:21:19.417
GARMADON:
No.

00:21:19.417 --> 00:21:21.417
Let them think
they’re winning.

00:21:21.417 --> 00:21:24.375
Uh, but I do not
understand.

00:21:24.375 --> 00:21:27.125
GARMADON:
Everything is going to plan.

00:21:27.125 --> 00:21:29.501
[GARMADON LAUGHS]

00:21:32.918 --> 00:21:35.751
<i>♪ Jump back, do it again ♪</i>

00:21:35.751 --> 00:21:36.584
<i>♪ Ninjago ♪</i>

00:21:36.584 --> 00:21:39.042
<i>♪ Ninjago ♪
♪ Come on, come on ♪</i>

00:21:39.042 --> 00:21:40.125
<i>♪ We gotta do it again ♪</i>

00:21:40.125 --> 00:21:43.834
<i>♪ We’ll just jump up
Kick back, whip around ♪</i>

00:21:43.834 --> 00:21:44.751
<i>♪ And spin ♪</i>

00:21:44.751 --> 00:21:47.667
<i>♪ And then we jump back
Do it again ♪</i>

00:21:47.667 --> 00:21:48.501
<i>♪ Ninjago ♪</i>

00:21:48.501 --> 00:21:50.918
<i>♪ Ninjago ♪
♪ Come on, come on ♪</i>

00:21:50.918 --> 00:21:53.042
<i>♪ Come on and together
We can win ♪</i>

00:21:53.042 --> 00:21:58.000
<i>♪ Jump up, kick back
Whip around and spin ♪</i>

